    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Tightly packed in this sense does not mean to override the byte length of values by trimming zero bytes. It means that if it's a \"strange\" type like a `uint24` or a `hash2` to not pad these values out to more \"normal\" lengths like 32 bits or 8 bytes.\r\n\r\nI think the language is pretty clear that types of known length should remain that length. I don't want to remove \"tightly packed\" entirely. Do you have an alternative suggestion for language here?",
